<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1429: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-15T15:00:00-05:00">October 15, 1931—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>48. Your 128, October 14, 5 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>] p.m., third
                            paragraph. Department does not desire you to visit Bolivia or Paraguay
                            at this time.</p>
                        <pb facs="0880" n="766" xml:id="pg_766"/>
                        <p>I much appreciate the action which Señor Izquierdo has taken in this
                            matter and would like to have you express to him my personal thanks for
                            his interest in the matter. Please tell him that Señor Cruchaga has also
                            been very helpful.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>